    <p>A form of vitamin B3, niacinamid­e is a fan favourite for its mul­ti­ple skin ben­e­fits – and be­cause it is deemed to be one of the safest and most sta­ble ac­tive in­gre­di­ents in skin­care.</p>
    <p>Safe to use in the day­time, it can be found in all cat­e­gories of prod­ucts, of­ten promis­ing bright­en­ing ben­e­fits.</p>
    <p>Niacinamid­e helps to re­duce ex­cess se­bum pro­duc­tion, im­prove the ap­pear­ance of pores and fine lines and strengthen the skin bar­rier.</p>
    <p>It also has anti-in­flam­ma­tory and an­tiox­i­dant prop­er­ties that help to re­duce dam­age done to the skin by ra­di­a­tion, in­clud­ing ul­tra­vi­o­let rays and blue light.</p>
    <p>TRY:</p>
    <p>1. Skin Inc My Daily Dose Of Ar­mour Serum, $98 2. Cau­dalie Vinop­er­fect Dark Spot Cor­rect­ing Mois­turiser, $75</p>

